===[[Season 1]]===
[[Petyr Baelish]] reminisces with [[Eddard Stark]] about how the latter's [[Brandon Stark (Son of Rickard)|brother]] injured him in a duel fought for the honor of [[Catelyn Stark|Catelyn Tully]] while he was a ward of Catelyn's [[Hoster Tully|father]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Lord Snow]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[Theon Greyjoy]] was given up by [[Balon Greyjoy|his father]] and surrendered to the custody of Lord [[Eddard Stark]] following Balon'sÂ [[Greyjoy Rebellion|failed rebellion]]. Although Theon was raised and educated by the [[House Stark|Starks]] and treated well, he was nevertheless a captive, something that rankles with him when [[Tyrion Lannister]] taunts him over the matter.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Following the arrest and execution of her father, [[Sansa Stark]] becomes a ward and hostage of Queen [[Cersei Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===

As part of a [[marriage]] alliance arranged by [[Tyrion Lannister]], Princess [[Myrcella Baratheon]] is taken to [[Sunspear]] as a ward of [[House Martell]] so she will get to know her betrothed, [[Trystane Martell]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Old Gods and the New]]&quot;,&lt;/ref&gt;
